<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>OOW Campaign Master Plan — Staff Training | Hearing Benefit Services</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Sans:wght@400;500;600;700&family=DM+Serif+Display&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
:root {
    --navy: #1a2744;
    --blue: #2563eb;
    --teal: #0d9488;
    --green: #16a34a;
    --orange: #ea580c;
    --red: #dc2626;
    --purple: #7c3aed;
    --gold: #d97706;
    --bg: #f8fafc;
    --card: #ffffff;
    --border: #e2e8f0;
    --text: #1e293b;
    --text-light: #64748b;
    --text-lighter: #94a3b8;
}
* { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
body { font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif; background: var(--bg); color: var(--text); line-height: 1.7; }
.header {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--navy) 0%, #2d3f63 100%);
    color: white; padding: 40px 24px; text-align: center;
}
.header img { max-width: 180px; margin-bottom: 16px; }
.header h1 { font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif; font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 6px; }
.header p { opacity: 0.85; font-size: 0.95rem; max-width: 620px; margin: 0 auto; }
.header .badge {
    display: inline-block; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.25);
    padding: 4px 14px; border-radius: 20px; font-size: 0.78rem; margin-top: 12px; letter-spacing: 0.5px;
}
.container { max-width: 880px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 32px 20px; }
.login-bar {
    background: #fffbeb; border: 1px solid #fde68a; border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 14px 20px; margin-bottom: 28px; font-size: 0.88rem; color: #92400e;
}
.login-bar strong { color: #78350f; }
.section-label {
    font-size: 0.72rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    color: var(--blue); margin-bottom: 6px;
}
.section-title {
    font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif; font-size: 1.6rem; margin-bottom: 16px; color: var(--navy);
}
.card {
    background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 28px; margin-bottom: 24px;
}
.card h3 { font-size: 1.15rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 10px; color: var(--navy); }
.card p, .card li { font-size: 0.92rem; color: var(--text); line-height: 1.7; }
.card ul { padding-left: 20px; margin-top: 8px; }
.card ul li { margin-bottom: 6px; }
.module-card {
    background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 14px;
    padding: 0; margin-bottom: 28px; overflow: hidden;
}
.module-header {
    padding: 20px 28px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); display: flex;
    align-items: center; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap;
}
.module-number {
    width: 42px; height: 42px; border-radius: 10px; display: flex; align-items: center;
    justify-content: center; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1.1rem; color: white; flex-shrink: 0;
}
.module-header h3 { font-size: 1.15rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--navy); flex: 1; }
.module-status {
    font-size: 0.72rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.8px;
    padding: 4px 12px; border-radius: 20px;
}
.status-live { background: #dcfce7; color: #166534; }
.status-built { background: #fef3c7; color: #92400e; }
.status-pending { background: #f1f5f9; color: #64748b; }
.module-body { padding: 24px 28px; }
.module-body p { font-size: 0.92rem; margin-bottom: 12px; }
.auto-badge, .manual-badge {
    display: inline-block; padding: 3px 10px; border-radius: 5px;
    font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.8px;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
}
.auto-badge { background: #dbeafe; color: #1e40af; }
.manual-badge { background: #fef3c7; color: #92400e; border: 1px solid #fde68a; }
.step-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 10px; padding: 18px 20px;
    margin-bottom: 14px; position: relative;
}
.step-card.auto-step { border-left: 4px solid var(--blue); background: #fafcff; }
.step-card.manual-step { border-left: 4px solid var(--orange); background: #fffcf5; }
.step-card .step-num {
    font-size: 0.72rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text-lighter);
    text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1px; margin-bottom: 4px;
}
.step-card h4 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 6px; color: var(--navy); }
.step-card p { font-size: 0.88rem; margin-bottom: 0; }
.manual-action-box {
    background: #fffbeb; border: 2px solid #f59e0b; border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 18px 20px; margin: 16px 0;
}
.manual-action-box h4 { font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 700; color: #92400e; margin-bottom: 8px; }
.manual-action-box ol { padding-left: 20px; font-size: 0.88rem; color: #78350f; }
.manual-action-box ol li { margin-bottom: 6px; line-height: 1.6; }
.manual-action-box .highlight { background: #fef3c7; padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px; font-weight: 600; }
.sms-box {
    background: #f0fdf4; border: 1px solid #bbf7d0; border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 16px 20px; margin: 12px 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: #166534;
    font-style: italic; line-height: 1.6;
}
.sms-label {
    font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1px;
    color: var(--teal); margin-bottom: 6px; font-style: normal;
}
.email-box {
    background: #eff6ff; border: 1px solid #bfdbfe; border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 16px 20px; margin: 12px 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: #1e40af; line-height: 1.6;
}
.email-label {
    font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1px;
    color: var(--blue); margin-bottom: 6px;
}
.tag {
    display: inline-block; padding: 4px 12px; border-radius: 6px; font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 600; font-family: 'DM Sans', monospace;
}
.tag-blue { background: #dbeafe; color: #1e40af; }
.tag-green { background: #dcfce7; color: #166534; }
.tag-orange { background: #ffedd5; color: #9a3412; }
.tag-red { background: #fee2e2; color: #991b1b; }
.tag-purple { background: #ede9fe; color: #5b21b6; }
.tag-teal { background: #ccfbf1; color: #115e59; }
.stage-list { margin: 12px 0; }
.stage-item {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; padding: 8px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #f1f5f9; font-size: 0.88rem;
}
.stage-item:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
.stage-num {
    width: 26px; height: 26px; border-radius: 6px; background: var(--navy); color: white;
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 700;
    flex-shrink: 0;
}
.info-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 12px 0; font-size: 0.88rem; }
.info-table th {
    text-align: left; background: #f1f5f9; padding: 10px 14px; font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--text-light); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px;
}
.info-table td { padding: 10px 14px; border-bottom: 1px solid #f1f5f9; }
.info-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
.alert { border-radius: 10px; padding: 14px 20px; margin: 16px 0; font-size: 0.88rem; }
.alert-info { background: #eff6ff; border: 1px solid #bfdbfe; color: #1e40af; }
.alert-warning { background: #fffbeb; border: 1px solid #fde68a; color: #92400e; }
.alert-success { background: #f0fdf4; border: 1px solid #bbf7d0; color: #166534; }
.divider { border: none; border-top: 2px solid var(--border); margin: 40px 0; }
.footer {
    background: var(--navy); color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); text-align: center;
    padding: 28px 20px; font-size: 0.82rem; margin-top: 40px;
}
.legend-box {
    display: flex; gap: 20px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin: 16px 0; padding: 16px 20px;
    background: #f8fafc; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 10px;
}
.legend-item { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; font-size: 0.85rem; }
.legend-dot { width: 14px; height: 14px; border-radius: 4px; flex-shrink: 0; }
@media (max-width: 600px) {
    .header h1 { font-size: 1.5rem; }
    .section-title { font-size: 1.3rem; }
    .module-header { padding: 16px 20px; }
    .module-body { padding: 18px 20px; }
    .card { padding: 20px; }
    .legend-box { flex-direction: column; gap: 10px; }
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- HEADER -->
<div class="header">
    <img src="https://assets.cdn.filesafe.space/UDKdmJIdT4xB1V6Lye64/media/68f7cb4d3a4642fd12cdeaab.png" alt="Hearing Benefit Services">
    <div style="font-size:0.78rem;opacity:0.7;margin-bottom:8px;">Staff Training · Confidential</div>
    <h1>OOW Campaign Master Plan</h1>
    <p>Complete training guide for the Out of Warranty Campaign — every workflow explained with clear labels showing what's automated and what Seteisha handles manually.</p>
    <div class="badge">Last Updated: May 2026</div>
</div>

<div class="container">

    <div class="login-bar">
        🔒 <strong>Staff Only.</strong> This page contains internal workflow details and SMS/email copy. Do not share outside the HBS team.
    </div>

    <!-- LEGEND -->
    <div class="card">
        <h3>How to Read This Guide</h3>
        <p>Every step in every workflow is labeled so you know exactly what GHL does automatically and what you need to do yourself.</p>
        <div class="legend-box">
            <div class="legend-item">
                <div class="legend-dot" style="background:var(--blue);"></div>
                <span><strong>AUTOMATED</strong> — GHL does this automatically. No action needed from you.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="legend-item">
                <div class="legend-dot" style="background:var(--orange);"></div>
                <span><strong>MANUAL — SETEISHA</strong> — You need to do this step yourself. Don't skip it.</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- OVERVIEW -->
    <div class="section-label">Overview</div>
    <div class="section-title">What Is the OOW Campaign?</div>
    <div class="card">
        <p>The <strong>Out of Warranty (OOW) Campaign</strong> is a multi-workflow system that proactively manages HBS patients whose hearing aids are approaching or past their warranty expiration date. The campaign runs inside GoHighLevel (GHL) using the <strong>Out of Warranty Lifecycle</strong> pipeline.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:12px;">The campaign has <strong>interconnected workflows</strong> that handle everything from initial outreach to warranty verification to upgrade sales — most steps are automated, with Seteisha stepping in only at critical decision points.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- PIPELINE STAGES -->
    <div class="section-label">Pipeline</div>
    <div class="section-title">Out of Warranty Lifecycle — Pipeline Stages</div>
    <div class="card">
        <p>Every OOW contact moves through these stages. GHL updates most stages automatically — Seteisha only needs to manually move contacts in rare situations where the workflow can't determine the next step.</p>
        <div class="stage-list">
            <div class="stage-item"><div class="stage-num">1</div> Warranty Check Sent</div>
            <div class="stage-item"><div class="stage-num">2</div> Awaiting Form Submission</div>
            <div class="stage-item"><div class="stage-num">3</div> Form Submitted — Pending Review</div>
            <div class="stage-item"><div class="stage-num">4</div> Warranty Verified — Active</div>
            <div class="stage-item"><div class="stage-num">5</div> Warranty Verified — Expired</div>
            <div class="stage-item"><div class="stage-num">6</div> OOW – 60 Days Out</div>
            <div class="stage-item"><div class="stage-num">7</div> OOW – 30 Days Out</div>
            <div class="stage-item"><div class="stage-num">8</div> OOW – Just Expired</div>
            <div class="stage-item"><div class="stage-num">9</div> Contacted – No Response</div>
            <div class="stage-item"><div class="stage-num">10</div> Engaged (Conversation Started)</div>
            <div class="stage-item"><div class="stage-num">11</div> Support Needed (Troubleshooting)</div>
            <div class="stage-item"><div class="stage-num">12</div> Repair in Progress</div>
            <div class="stage-item"><div class="stage-num">13</div> Upgrade Opportunity</div>
            <div class="stage-item"><div class="stage-num">14</div> Warranty Extension Offered</div>
            <div class="stage-item"><div class="stage-num">15</div> Appointment Booked</div>
            <div class="stage-item"><div class="stage-num">16</div> Converted (Won)</div>
            <div class="stage-item"><div class="stage-num">17</div> Not Interested / Lost</div>
            <div class="stage-item"><div class="stage-num">18</div> Recycle (90-Day Nurture)</div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ALL TAGS -->
    <div class="section-label">Tags</div>
    <div class="section-title">All OOW Contact Tags</div>
    <div class="card">
        <p>Tags marked <span class="manual-badge">MANUAL</span> must be added by Seteisha. Tags marked <span class="auto-badge">AUTOMATED</span> are applied by GHL workflows — never add these manually.</p>
        <table class="info-table" style="margin-top:16px;">
            <thead><tr><th>Tag</th><th>Who Adds It</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr><td><span class="tag tag-blue">warranty_check_sent</span></td><td><span class="manual-badge">MANUAL — Seteisha</span></td><td>Triggers Warranty Status Check Blast workflow</td></tr>
                <tr><td><span class="tag tag-teal">warranty_form_submitted</span></td><td><span class="auto-badge">AUTOMATED</span></td><td>Patient submitted the warranty check form</td></tr>
                <tr><td><span class="tag tag-green">OOW_ACTIVE</span></td><td><span class="manual-badge">MANUAL — Seteisha</span></td><td>Warranty verified as ACTIVE in Signia portal</td></tr>
                <tr><td><span class="tag tag-red">OOW_EXPIRED</span></td><td><span class="manual-badge">MANUAL — Seteisha</span></td><td>Warranty verified as EXPIRED in Signia portal</td></tr>
                <tr><td><span class="tag tag-blue">OOW_60</span></td><td><span class="auto-badge">AUTOMATED</span></td><td>Triggers 60-Day Pre-Expiration sequence — auto-applied 60 days before Warranty End Date when Seteisha enters the date</td></tr>
                <tr><td><span class="tag tag-blue">OOW_30</span></td><td><span class="auto-badge">AUTOMATED</span></td><td>Triggers 30-Day Pre-Expiration sequence — auto-applied 30 days before Warranty End Date when Seteisha enters the date</td></tr>
                <tr><td><span class="tag tag-orange">OOW_ENGAGED</span></td><td><span class="auto-badge">AUTOMATED</span></td><td>Patient replied to any OOW message</td></tr>
                <tr><td><span class="tag tag-purple">OOW_NO_RESPONSE</span></td><td><span class="auto-badge">AUTOMATED</span></td><td>No reply after full sequence completed</td></tr>
                <tr><td><span class="tag tag-orange">OOW_UPGRADE</span></td><td><span class="auto-badge">AUTOMATED</span></td><td>Expired warranty — upgrade candidate</td></tr>
                <tr><td><span class="tag tag-teal">OOW_WARRANTY</span></td><td><span class="manual-badge">MANUAL — Seteisha</span></td><td>Warranty extension candidate</td></tr>
                <tr><td><span class="tag tag-teal">OOW_REPAIR</span></td><td><span class="manual-badge">MANUAL — Seteisha</span></td><td>Patient needs a repair</td></tr>
                <tr><td><span class="tag tag-green">OOW_BOOKED</span></td><td><span class="auto-badge">AUTOMATED</span></td><td>Appointment scheduled</td></tr>
                <tr><td><span class="tag tag-green">OOW_CONVERTED</span></td><td><span class="manual-badge">MANUAL — Seteisha</span></td><td>Sale or service completed</td></tr>
                <tr><td><span class="tag tag-purple">OOW_RECYCLE</span></td><td><span class="auto-badge">AUTOMATED</span></td><td>In 90-day nurture loop</td></tr>
                <tr><td><span class="tag tag-red">opted_out</span></td><td><span class="auto-badge">AUTOMATED</span></td><td>Replied STOP — do not contact</td></tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        <div class="alert alert-warning" style="margin-top:16px;">
            <strong>⚠️ Rule:</strong> Never manually add a tag marked AUTOMATED. These are applied by GHL workflows and adding them manually can cause duplicate messages or workflow conflicts.
        </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="divider">

    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <!-- WORKFLOW 1: WARRANTY STATUS CHECK BLAST -->
    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <div class="section-label">Workflow 1</div>
    <div class="section-title">Warranty Status Check Blast</div>

    <div class="module-card">
        <div class="module-header">
            <div class="module-number" style="background:var(--blue);">1</div>
            <h3>HBS — Warranty Status Check Blast</h3>
            <span class="module-status status-live">✓ LIVE</span>
        </div>
        <div class="module-body">
            <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Sends a 4-message outreach sequence over 14 days to existing patients asking about their warranty status. When a patient replies, they receive an auto-reply with the warranty check form link, and Seteisha gets a task notification.</p>
            <h3 style="margin-top:20px;">Step-by-Step Breakdown</h3>
            <div class="step-card manual-step">
                <div class="step-num">Before the Workflow</div>
                <span class="manual-badge">MANUAL — Seteisha</span>
                <h4>Seteisha Adds the Tag to Start the Campaign</h4>
                <p>Seteisha selects contacts from the patient list and adds the tag <code>warranty_check_sent</code>. This triggers the entire workflow. Once the tag is added, the system takes over and sends the first SMS automatically.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card auto-step">
                <div class="step-num">Day 1</div>
                <span class="auto-badge">AUTOMATED</span>
                <h4>Day 1 SMS Sent to Patient</h4>
                <p>GHL creates an opportunity in the Out of Warranty Lifecycle pipeline and sends the first SMS automatically.</p>
                <div class="sms-box">
                    <div class="sms-label">Day 1 SMS</div>
                    Hi {{contact.first_name}}, this is Hearing Benefit Services. We're reaching out to check in on your hearing aids — do you know if they are still under warranty? We can look this up for you at no charge. Simply reply to this message and we'll take care of it. Reply STOP to opt out.
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card auto-step">
                <div class="step-num">Day 3 (if no reply)</div>
                <span class="auto-badge">AUTOMATED</span>
                <h4>Day 3 Email Sent</h4>
                <p>If the patient hasn't replied to the Day 1 SMS, GHL sends a follow-up email using the "Warranty Check Blast — Day 3 Email" template.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card auto-step">
                <div class="step-num">Day 7 (if no reply)</div>
                <span class="auto-badge">AUTOMATED</span>
                <h4>Day 7 SMS Sent</h4>
                <p>Second SMS reminder sent automatically.</p>
                <div class="sms-box">
                    <div class="sms-label">Day 7 SMS</div>
                    Hi {{contact.first_name}}, just a quick follow-up from Hearing Benefit Services. Most hearing aids have a 1–3 year warranty and many patients don't know when theirs expires. We can check this for you — just reply and we'll look it up. Reply STOP to opt out.
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card auto-step">
                <div class="step-num">Day 14 (if no reply)</div>
                <span class="auto-badge">AUTOMATED</span>
                <h4>Day 14 Final SMS Sent</h4>
                <p>Last follow-up message. If no reply after 7 more days, contact is tagged <code>OOW_NO_RESPONSE</code> and moved to "Contacted — No Response" stage.</p>
                <div class="sms-box">
                    <div class="sms-label">Day 14 Final SMS</div>
                    Hi {{contact.first_name}}, last follow-up from Hearing Benefit Services. If your hearing aids are out of warranty, repairs and replacements become out-of-pocket costs. We're happy to check your warranty status for free — just reply YES and we'll get started. Reply STOP to opt out.
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card auto-step" style="border-left-color:var(--teal);">
                <div class="step-num">When Patient Replies (any time)</div>
                <span class="auto-badge">AUTOMATED</span>
                <h4>Auto-Reply + Form Link + Task for Seteisha</h4>
                <p>When a patient replies to ANY of the 4 messages, GHL automatically:</p>
                <ul style="padding-left:20px;margin-top:8px;font-size:0.88rem;">
                    <li>Sends an auto-reply SMS with the warranty form link</li>
                    <li>Updates the opportunity to "Awaiting Form Submission"</li>
                    <li>Creates a task for Seteisha: "[Name] replied to Warranty Check Blast — Send Form"</li>
                </ul>
                <div class="sms-box" style="margin-top:12px;">
                    <div class="sms-label">Auto-Reply SMS</div>
                    Hi {{contact.first_name}}, thank you for reaching out to Hearing Benefit Services! One of our hearing specialists will be in touch shortly to help check your warranty status. In the meantime, you can fill out a quick form here so we can get started: https://hearingbenefitservices.com/outofwarrantyform
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="manual-action-box">
                <h4>👋 Seteisha — What You Need to Do for This Workflow</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Check your GHL task list daily.</strong> When a patient replies to the warranty blast, you'll see a task with their name and phone number.</li>
                    <li><strong>Review the patient's reply</strong> in GHL Conversations. See what they said — some may ask questions, others may just say "yes."</li>
                    <li><strong>Follow up within 15 minutes</strong> during business hours. Call or text them to make sure they fill out the warranty check form.</li>
                    <li><strong>If the patient doesn't fill out the form within 1-2 days,</strong> follow up again to remind them. The form link is: <a href="https://hearingbenefitservices.com/outofwarrantyform" target="_blank">hearingbenefitservices.com/outofwarrantyform</a></li>
                    <li><strong>Once the patient submits the form,</strong> Workflow 2 (Form Submission Handler) takes over automatically — see below.</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <!-- WORKFLOW 2: WARRANTY FORM SUBMISSION HANDLER -->
    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <div class="section-label">Workflow 2</div>
    <div class="section-title">Warranty Form Submission Handler</div>

    <div class="module-card">
        <div class="module-header">
            <div class="module-number" style="background:var(--teal);">2</div>
            <h3>HBS — Warranty Form Submission Handler</h3>
            <span class="module-status status-live">✓ LIVE</span>
        </div>
        <div class="module-body">
            <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> When a patient submits the warranty check form, this workflow automatically tags them, updates the pipeline, creates a task for Seteisha with all the device details, and logs the form data to the contact record.</p>
            <h3 style="margin-top:20px;">Step-by-Step Breakdown</h3>
            <div class="step-card auto-step">
                <div class="step-num">Trigger</div>
                <span class="auto-badge">AUTOMATED</span>
                <h4>Patient Submits the Warranty Check Form</h4>
                <p>The patient fills out the form at <a href="https://hearingbenefitservices.com/outofwarrantyform" target="_blank">hearingbenefitservices.com/outofwarrantyform</a> with their device model, serial numbers, purchase date, and brand. The moment they hit submit, this workflow fires.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card auto-step">
